lumen-argus-proxy — third-party rule-content attribution
=========================================================

The rules in this directory (community.json) include patterns adapted from
Gitleaks (https://github.com/gitleaks/gitleaks), licensed under the MIT
License. The upstream license text is reproduced in LICENSE-gitleaks.txt
alongside this notice.

Adapted rules carry the "gitleaks" tag in community.json so they can be
enumerated programmatically. As of 0.1.0 the set is:

  digitalocean_access_token, digitalocean_pat, digitalocean_refresh_token,
  cloudflare_api_key, cloudflare_global_api_key, cloudflare_origin_ca_key,
  linear_api_key, linear_client_secret,
  notion_api_token,
  atlassian_api_token,
  kubernetes_secret_yaml,
  shopify_access_token, shopify_private_app_token,
  hubspot_api_key,
  telegram_bot_token

For full project-level attribution including runtime dependencies, see
the NOTICE.md at the lumen-argus repository root.
